reviews.review_text: bread crumb Jack Straw, according to The DeadLists Project, was played 476 times.  429 of those were first set.  Without looking at each show, I can't tell exactly how many times it ended a set, but I know there are very few.  I think it ends in a way that begs to be followed, which is probably why it predominantly opened sets.
